<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>EveCommander Install & User Guide</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            color-scheme: dark;
        }

        body {
            margin: 0;
            font-family: "Segoe UI", Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            background: radial-gradient(circle at top, #1f2937 0%, #111827 50%, #0b1020 100%);
            color: #e5e7eb;
            padding: 24px;
        }

        .container {
            width: min(1100px, 100%);
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        .hero {
            background: rgba(17, 24, 39, 0.93);
            border: 1px solid #374151;
            border-radius: 14px;
            box-shadow: 0 12px 36px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
            padding: 24px;
            margin-bottom: 16px;
        }

        h1 {
            margin: 0 0 8px;
            color: #f9fafb;
            font-size: 2rem;
        }

        h2 {
            margin: 0 0 12px;
            color: #f9fafb;
            font-size: 1.3rem;
        }

        h3 {
            margin: 0 0 8px;
            color: #f3f4f6;
            font-size: 1.05rem;
        }

        p {
            margin: 0 0 14px;
            color: #d1d5db;
            line-height: 1.55;
        }

        ol {
            margin: 0 0 18px;
            padding-left: 20px;
            color: #e5e7eb;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        ul {
            margin: 0 0 14px;
            padding-left: 20px;
            color: #d1d5db;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        li {
            margin-bottom: 4px;
        }

        .grid {
            display: grid;
            gap: 16px;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr));
        }

        .card {
            background: rgba(17, 24, 39, 0.93);
            border: 1px solid #374151;
            border-radius: 14px;
            box-shadow: 0 10px 28px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
            padding: 20px;
        }

        .banner {
            border: 1px solid #14532d;
            background: rgba(22, 101, 52, 0.2);
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 12px;
            margin: 12px 0 16px;
        }

        .banner ul {
            margin-bottom: 0;
        }

        .actions {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            gap: 12px;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }

        .btn {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            padding: 10px 14px;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border: 1px solid #4b5563;
            background: rgba(55, 65, 81, 0.9);
            color: #e5e7eb;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .btn-primary {
            border-color: #2563eb;
            background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.85);
            color: #f9fafb;
        }

        .muted {
            color: #9ca3af;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <main class="container">
        <section class="hero">
            <h1>Install EveCommander</h1>
            <p class="muted">Read-only intelligence gathering and monitoring for EVE Online multi-client operations.</p>

            <div class="banner">
                <h3>⚠️ EULA Compliance</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>✅ Read-only UI/memory parsing</li>
                    <li>✅ No automation, no input simulation, no bot behavior</li>
                    <li>✅ Information and monitoring only</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>Install Steps</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Download the EveCommander ZIP package.</li>
                <li>Extract the ZIP to a folder of your choice.</li>
                <li>Run <strong>Commander.exe</strong>.</li>
                <li>Launch your EVE Online client(s).</li>
            </ol>

            <div class="actions">
                <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Kjd-Mf_2lsmlJu12XjwOTshcCDRU3FgF/view?usp=drive_link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Download ZIP</a>
                <a class="btn" href="<%= fix_path('/') %>">Back to Dashboards</a>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="grid">
            <article class="card">
                <h2>System Requirements</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Windows 10/11 (64-bit)</li>
                    <li>.NET 9.0 Runtime</li>
                    <li>EVE Online client(s)</li>
                </ul>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
                <h2>Quick Start</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Start EveCommander and your EVE clients.</li>
                    <li>Wait for clients to be detected in Commander (slow process!).</li>
                    <li>Enable plugins as required in Plugin Selector.</li>
                    <li>Click "Start".</li>
                </ol>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
                <h2>Global Hotkeys</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Ctrl+F8</strong>: Stop monitoring all clients</li>
                    <li><strong>Backslash (\)</strong>: Cycle Eve client windows to front</li>
                </ul>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
                <h2>Optional Plugin Types</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Character-specific</strong>: enable per character</li>
                    <li><strong>Auto-run</strong>: start when client is detected</li>
                    <li><strong>Global</strong>: operate across all clients</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="muted">Examples: GridScout, LocalIntel, KeepstarWatcher.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
                <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Remember; ctrl+F8 stops monitoring all clients.</li>
                    <li>Red plugin status means error; error message should be shown.</li>
                    <li>Green plugin status means that plugin thinks it has finished!</li>
                    <li>Keep important UI elements visible for reliable parsing.</li>
                    <li>Plugins wont show in the list until at least one Eve Client has been detected fully.</li>
                </ul>
            </article>

            <article class="card">
                <h2>FAQ</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Safe to use?</strong> We believe so — read-only by design.</li>
                    <li><strong>Can it control ships?</strong> No, never.</li>
                    <li><strong>How often is a client checked?</strong> About every 3 seconds.</li>
                    <li><strong>Can you speed up startup?</strong> Unfortunately, no. But it is cached so just don't close your game client often.</li>
                    <li><strong>Mac/Linux?</strong> No, Windows only.</li>
                </ul>
            </article>
        </section>

        <section class="hero" style="margin-top: 16px;">
            <h2>Support & Source</h2>
            <p>For support, troubleshooting and contribution details, see the EveCommander repository.</p>
            <div class="actions">
                <a class="btn" href="https://github.com/LakMoore/EveCommander" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open GitHub Repository</a>
            </div>
            <p class="muted" style="margin-top: 12px;">Fly safe o7</p>
        </section>
    </main>
</body>

</html>
